social_posts.post_text:
How before any of y’all @ me, let me just say this….

YES I love me some country music.
YES country is what gets my hyped while I’m lifting.
YES some other times I’ll listen to pop.
YES I will always circle back to country.

💥 pow pow 💥 

Biggest piece of advice I can give while & about training is to not forget one very crucial piece…..

HAVE FRIGGIN FUN! 

Love you mean it.
Xox Chlo

🍌
This week Oly has had me some sort of way. Very challenging for me and just what I needed, my life is feeling upside down but being able to focus on my training at the start of the day has really kept my mental health in a good spot.
🫒
I have been working on narrowing my grip while doing OHS action and I’m friggin living for it.
Yes - my arms bed like that, it’s a thing. Cute right 💁🏻‍♀️
🌪️
No - I wasn’t winching @ dropping the dang barbell. It was a whole body feeling after that last complex. 🏴‍☠️
🔮
10/10 recommend pushing yourself outside of your comfort zone on a daily basis.
⚙️
Xox 
Chlo
🧽Dang, I felt that in my whole a$$ body🧽
Pow Pow

🎠
I’ll take 195 for a ride anytime
⛲️
I’m really not sure what I do with my head before I front squat but it makes me wonder if I’ve been reincarnated from a bard at some point 💁🏻‍♀️
(The things that go through my head for no particular reason at all)
🫧

🧽A few things about taking 98% for a ride🧽
A) Gotta make sure that bar & rack are stable
B) Step in long to ensure rack & shoulder stabilization
C) state at my feet and wiggle my toes to make sure the ground isn’t gonna move
D) Hair flip to ensure proper neck mobility
E) Grunt to get the bar off of the rack
F) Step back cautiously while checking out the physique in the mirror
G) finally, just move the friggin weight 😬
🫧
Who else has a long drawn out set up 💁🏻‍♀️

👌🏼last set of 5 and this was a major friggin woof! 🦴
3 cleans + 1 jerk @ 71kgs
⚖️ @ 64kgs

📚Bookend’it baby📚
✏️
A few things going through my head while I’m lifting.
1️⃣
I’m wearing black camo, do you think if the lights were off you’d be able to see me? 👻
2️⃣
I’m not sure why I look down when I’m doing high reps, I guess maybe I’m looking to see if my soul is seeping out 💧
3️⃣
Don’t @ me about “form & looking down”, cause I really don’t give a flying heck 😘 
4️⃣
Love yah, mean it.
Xox Chlo

Check-in day came once again with @kelskiel 
❣️
I’ve never struggled with weight loss and management but I have struggled greatly with body image issues. In my humble opinion, having body image issues runs rapid through the fitness, health & wellness community and not many of us talk about them. Over the years I’ve had moments of great security with how I’ve viewed myself and there have been other times that, well quite the opposite was true.
♥️
I can not stress how important it has been to have a nutrition coach in my life to bounce my thoughts off of when it comes to food, performance and my body image.
♥️
My 2¢ of knowledge here is that you don’t need to have a nutrition coach (but it can help) as long as you have at least 1 friend you can chat about your nutrition/body image issues with. It might not solve the problem but it sure as hell takes some of the power out of the negative self talk.
♥️
Haven’t said it in a while,
Love you mean it.
Xox Chlo

Y’all I could not be happier at the moment. Last night I not only hit a current PR but I also hit a lifetime PR. Bested my snatch by 2.4 lbs bringing me to a whopping 162.4 lbs / 73.5kg ! Which means I’m now only 2.5 kg from my lifetime goal. Guess I’m gonna have to set a new goal soon, I’ll wait till I hit 75kg to figure that one out 💁🏻‍♀️
💥
There is something to be said about trading with partners or a club. 95% of the time I am training by myself, so getting to lift with this group & my coach weekly has been a game changer for me.
💥
Any who, I’m gonna continue to jump for joy every time I do something the stokes me out. Why, well cause if I wanna get ahead I have got to be my biggest fan!
💥
And yes, my precious baby angel Axel likes no fun. Especially if people run up on me, regardless if it’s celebration 🤣

I had such a blast competing this weekend, my first time competing in 7 years. This gal shook out them rusty joints & did the thing!
💥
I had been down with a back injury for almost 2 weeks prior to the meet and went in cautiously & with realistic expeditions. Originally I had planned to go for heavier numbers, talked it out with my coach and literally took it lift by lift. We played it very conservatively and I hit 80% of my intended snatch & 85% of my intended clean & jerk, which I am very satisfied with.
💥
So here I am, one more week of recovery for my back and then I’ll be right back at it getting ready for the next meet.
💥
I don’t have one highlight I want to share but I have an overall highlight for sure. And that highlight is that the energy in the warm up room and main floor was absolutely amazing from beginning to end. Saw some old friends and made a couple new ones. There really is no comparison to the camaraderie one feels in the weightlifting Community (sorry about it to all my cf friends)!
💥
Looking forward to the rest of the season and being able to move some weights around with all my pals.
💥
Love y’all, mean it!
Xox Chlo 
💥
Ps
No music needed, the energy of the crowd is enough for me 🖤🌬️🌪️
Pps
Shout out to my coach for not only wrangling the entire team, but simultaneously getting vids and competing himself.

Today’s a day of wagging tails and slobbery kisses (& some tears), because it’s Axel’s 8th birthday! Can you believe it? We’ve been inseparable for 7 years and 4 magical months. It’s been an adventure of epic proportions - 7 glorious trips around the sun, oodles of feel-good moments, thousands of treat-induced struggle cuddles, over 50 flights, 10 states, a gazillion cities, and more hotel beds than I can count. We’ve greeted countless pre-dawn mornings together and navigated through some real tough friggin ish, like trauma recovery and that one time he heroically stood between danger and me (when a delusional man was threatening us with a knife). And let’s not forget his miraculous escape from a semi truck encounter with just a few scratches - seriously, thank the stars!
♥️🐕♥️
When Axel charged full speed into my life, little did I know he’d become my live-in, four-legged grounding rod , bodyguard, and bestie all rolled into one. Our bond is something out of a stupid feel good Anne Hathaway / Angelina Jolie fairy tale. He’s got this sixth sense, always knowing how to be there for me in ways I never could have anticipated that I needed. We’re like two peas in a pod; when we’re apart, I swear a piece of my heart feels missing. I never imagined one soul could bring so much laughter, comfort, and security into my life. The universe must have been in a really good mood the day it decided to send him my way.
🐕
Axel, my goofy, lovable Badaxel, my zoopy loopy dog-faced boi, you’re more than just a pet - you’re my heart on four paws. Happy Birthday, my precious baby angel! Here’s to many more tail-wagging, treat-filled adventures together! 
🩶🐩🩶
And yes I cried 1-10 times while writing this 😭
